main event: A cylindrical, white object reflecting the sun was observed for 2-3 seconds, moving in a straight line at a moderately fast speed.
interesting points: The object was described as looking like a baseball bat.
The witness was an ex-USAF pilot and engineer who observed the object through 7-power German binoculars.
The object faded from sight after about 45 minutes of observation.
The report includes wind data from the Watertown area.
